Description: Rim and body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery open vessel, probably a plate; shallow body with flat floor and offset rim; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between grey-buff margins, with some mica inclusions; worn dark grey slip on exterior, completely lost on interior; inscription on exterior of rim.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.100)
